<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Kelly Brook looked sensational on Saturday as she made the most of the sunny weather after another day on air for her Heart Radio show. </p>

<p>The presenter, 40, put on a very leggy display for her radio work at the Global Studios in London, wearing a pair of tiny ripped denim hotpants with frayed hems.</p>

<p>Kelly teamed the item of clothing with a burnt copper ruffled top with tassels on the neckline.</p>

<p>Leggy! Kelly Brook looked sensational on Saturday as she made the most of the sunny weather after another day on air for her Heart Radio show</p>

<p>Finishing her boho-chic ensemble, the model opted for a pair of suede cowboy ankle boots with tassel detailing.</p>

<p>Adding some glamorous touches, Kelly finished her look with a black Chanel quilted handbag with a gold chain.</p>

<p>The presenter appeared to go makeup-free as she displayed her age-defying features and swept her brunette locks into a high ponytail.</p>

<p>Kelly appeared in great spirits after her radio duties and flashed a smile as she made her way home.   </p>

<p>The star's outing comes as she admitted she's 'not worried' about her 'weight creeping up'.</p>

<p>Another day on air! The presenter, 40, put on a very leggy display for her radio work at the Global Studios in London, wearing a pair of tiny ripped denim hotpants with frayed hems</p>

<p>Details: Kelly teamed the item of clothing with a burnt copper ruffled top with tassels on the neckline</p>

<p>She also declared 'diets shouldn't be about deprivation', after revealing she shed a whopping two stone in March.</p>

<p>While she has been keeping busy by exercising at home, her diet consists of 'healthy, low-calorie meals' with sweet treats such as popcorn and homemade fruit lollies.</p>

<p>The brunette has been candid about her weight fluctuating, with the bombshell slimming down to a size 10-12 after going to a size 16.</p>

<p>On her current figure, she told new! magazine: 'I'm a real foodie and enjoy cooking. I wasn't surprised at all to see my weight creep up a little over the last few weeks.</p>

<p>'[I've gained] a few pounds, but I'm not worried. I know I can lean on the SlimFast 3.2.1. Plan to deal with my weight loss ups and downs, so I can get back on track.</p>

<p>'It's easy and it works. Diets shouldn't be about deprivation - they need to be sustainable after all.'</p>

<p>Home time! Kelly appeared in great spirits after her radio duties and flashed a smile as she made her way home</p>
